---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Programmatic Remnant Banner Inventory for Ad Networks | AdBunny"
  description="Access aggregated remnant banner inventory programmatically. AI-optimized placement, real-time performance data, no manual tuning required."
  keywords="programmatic banner inventory access, remnant inventory for advertisers, ad network demand partner, real-time bidding banner ads"
>

<section class="min-h-[85vh] flex items-center" style="border-bottom:1px solid var(--color-border)">
  <div class="max-w-[80rem] mx-auto px-8 py-32 max-md:py-20 w-full">
    <p class="kicker mb-8">For Ad Networks</p>
    <h1 class="font-serif leading-[1.08] tracking-tight mb-6" style="font-size:clamp(2.5rem,5vw,4rem);font-weight:550">programmatic access to aggregated remnant banner inventory</h1>
    <p class="text-base leading-relaxed mb-10 max-w-[34rem]" style="color:var(--color-text-secondary)">AdBunny gives ad networks, DSPs, and media buyers efficient access to remnant banner inventory across our publisher network, with AI-driven placement optimization and real-time performance reporting.</p>
    <a href="/contact" class="btn btn-primary btn-lg">Talk to Our Demand Team</a>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="py-32 max-md:py-20" style="border-bottom:1px solid var(--color-border)">
  <div class="max-w-[80rem] mx-auto px-8">
    <p class="kicker mb-12">The problem</p>
    <div class="grid grid-cols-2 gap-20 max-md:grid-cols-1 max-md:gap-12">
      <div>
        <h2 class="font-serif leading-[1.08] tracking-tight mb-6" style="font-size:clamp(2rem,4vw,3rem);font-weight:550">the scale problem with remnant inventory</h2>
      </div>
      <div>
        <p class="text-base leading-relaxed" style="color:var(--color-text-secondary)">Remnant inventory is valuable, but it's fragmented across thousands of individual publishers, each with different setups, fill patterns, and placement quality. Accessing it efficiently and optimizing performance across it doesn't scale with manual processes.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="py-32 max-md:py-20" style="border-bottom:1px solid var(--color-border)">
  <div class="max-w-[80rem] mx-auto px-8">
    <p class="kicker mb-12">How it works</p>
    <h2 class="font-serif leading-[1.08] tracking-tight mb-16 max-md:mb-10" style="font-size:clamp(2rem,4vw,3rem);font-weight:550">how AdBunny solves it</h2>
    <div class="grid grid-cols-3 gap-12 max-md:grid-cols-1">
      <div style="border-top:1px solid var(--color-border);padding-top:1.5rem">
        <div class="font-serif text-sm mb-6" style="color:var(--color-text-tertiary)">01</div>
        <h3 class="font-serif text-xl tracking-tight mb-3" style="font-weight:550">aggregated access</h3>
        <p class="text-sm leading-relaxed" style="color:var(--color-text-secondary)">Reach remnant banner inventory across the AdBunny publisher network through a single integration, instead of negotiating site by site.</p>
      </div>
      <div style="border-top:1px solid var(--color-border);padding-top:1.5rem">
        <div class="font-serif text-sm mb-6" style="color:var(--color-text-tertiary)">02</div>
        <h3 class="font-serif text-xl tracking-tight mb-3" style="font-weight:550">AI-optimized placement</h3>
        <p class="text-sm leading-relaxed" style="color:var(--color-text-secondary)">AdBunny's optimization layer continuously improves banner performance across placements without requiring manual tuning on your end.</p>
      </div>
      <div style="border-top:1px solid var(--color-border);padding-top:1.5rem">
        <div class="font-serif text-sm mb-6" style="color:var(--color-text-tertiary)">03</div>
        <h3 class="font-serif text-xl tracking-tight mb-3" style="font-weight:550">real-time reporting</h3>
        <p class="text-sm leading-relaxed" style="color:var(--color-text-secondary)">Get placement-level performance data as it happens, so you can evaluate spend efficiency and adjust strategy with current information.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="py-32 max-md:py-20" style="border-bottom:1px solid var(--color-border)">
  <div class="max-w-[80rem] mx-auto px-8">
    <p class="kicker mb-12">Who this is for</p>
    <div class="max-w-[40rem]">
      <p class="text-base leading-relaxed" style="color:var(--color-text-secondary)">Ad networks, DSPs, and media buyers looking to deploy banner campaigns efficiently against remnant inventory at scale, with data to back up performance decisions.</p>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="py-32 max-md:py-20 text-center">
  <div class="max-w-[80rem] mx-auto px-8">
    <h2 class="font-serif leading-[1.08] tracking-tight mb-6" style="font-size:clamp(2rem,4vw,3rem);font-weight:550">get efficient access to remnant banner demand</h2>
    <p class="text-base mb-10" style="color:var(--color-text-secondary)">Talk to our team about integrating with the AdBunny network.</p>
    <a href="/" class="btn btn-primary btn-lg">Talk to Our Demand Team</a>
  </div>
</section>
